snippet: An analysis revealed that the botched rollout of Florida’s online system for unemployment claims may have kept jobless Floridians from receiving $20 million in benefits during October and November.
abstract: Informal analysis by the National Employment Law Project, workers' rights group, finds botched rollout of Florida's online system for unemployment claims may have kept jobless residents from receiving $20 million in benefits in October and November 2013.
lead_paragraph: An analysis revealed that the botched rollout of Florida’s online system for unemployment claims may have kept jobless Floridians from receiving $20 million in benefits during October and November.

headline.main: Florida’s Site Said to Delay Millions in Aid to Jobless
headline.print_headline: Florida’s Site Said to Delay Millions in Aid to Jobless
